--   Two ⊢⊢ spawners fire at different levels: outline → scenes → beats.
--   This mirrors narrative structure: story is composed of acts, acts of
--   scenes, scenes of beats. The spawner pattern naturally expresses
--   recursive composition — each level uses a template to generate
--   the next level down.
--
-- ⊢= Observation 2: bottom-up assembly preserves local coherence
--   Beats are written with scene context. Scenes are written with act
--   context. Assembly goes bottom-up: beats → scenes → story. Each
--   level is locally coherent (beats match their scene's emotional arc,
--   scenes match their act's summary). Cross-level consistency is checked
--   only at the top (check-consistency), not at every level. This is
--   efficient: O(1) consistency checks instead of O(N).
--
-- ⊢= Observation 3: confluence enables massively parallel story generation
--   All 8 scene cells are independent (frame 3-10). All 19 beat cells are
--   independent (frames 12-30). In a parallel runtime, 27 of 34 cells
--   could execute concurrently. Only the assembly and consistency cells
--   are sequential barriers. Narrative generation is embarrassingly parallel
--   at every level except final assembly.
--
-- ⊢= Observation 4: beat-type classification enables rhythm analysis
--   Beat types (action, dialogue, internal, description, revelation) create
--   a structural fingerprint: Scene 1.2 is [description→description→revelation],
--   Scene 2.2 is [action→dialogue→internal]. This enables automated rhythm
--   checking — too many consecutive dialogue beats might indicate talking-head
--   syndrome; too many description beats might indicate pacing drag.
--
-- ⊢= Observation 5: the consistency oracle catches cross-level seams
--   Issues I1 and I2 are both about transitions between independently
--   generated scenes — exactly the seams you'd expect from parallel
--   generation. The consistency oracle catches what confluence doesn't
--   guarantee: narrative flow across independently computed boundaries.
--   This is the trade-off of parallel generation: local coherence is free,
--   global coherence requires a top-level pass.
